-- 
Real Madrid Replaces Cup Ramos Dropped Under Bus, AP Reports

-- B y   C l e m e n t i n e   F l e t c h e r
-- 
2011-04-22T14:16:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-22/real-madrid-replaces-cup-ramos-dropped-under-bus-ap-reports.html
Real Madrid soccer club has
replaced the Copa del Rey cup that was crushed after defender
 Sergio Ramos  dropped it under a bus,  Associated Press  reported,
citing the maker of the trophy.  Real Madrid has sent the replacement to its trophy museum,
according to the report. The team defeated Barcelona 1-0 on
April 20, winning the tournament for the first time in 18 years.
Ramos dropped the cup from the top of the team bus while
celebrating the victory.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Clementine Fletcher in London 
 cfletcher5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at 
 cperri@bloomberg.net . 